reviews.text: Comfortable and affordable cafe. Nice place to take a rest after hiking on Lamma Island.

We had the mini spinach pizza with fries and salad. it's very overpriced for what it was: poorly presented, the pizzas were tiny (size of a biscuit x 4) and undercooked, with literally 6 or 7 fries and 1 piece of lettuce with a slice of tomato. All for the price of $72 + 10% included in the bill. Will not visit again.

result.name: Lamma Rainbow Seafood Restaurant

reviews.text: Best seafood place of Hongkong. Authentic style, best taste, great stuff. A place you will definitely remember! No idea how someone could give less than five stars. We had lunch and dinner at the first day here as it was too nice to leave this place without a second meal. Go there and be satisfied! A must when you are in this area.

Likely the best seafood in all of Hong Kong.  Been here many times and the food is always excellent.  A wonderful afternoon or evening out.  The scallops served in shells are particularly amazing.  Super friendly service.  You won't be disappointed.

Great service. Seafood all seemed fresh and healthy! Food was pretty good but a little expensive (most along the strip are the same though). Be careful of the tea and sauces they put on the table - they are extra charge. 
Offers free ferry back to central which is great.

Awesome food. Great atmosphere and a free ferry back to Hong Kong.  What more could you ask for.  Make sure you spend some time hiking around the island to work up an appetite. The scenery is amazing!
Very decent seafood place in Lamma Island. Set menu for 6 people hkd1498 plus 10% charge and drinks. Good quality and portion is big enough for 6 people. Recommended!

À éviter !!! Ils font gonfler la note finale de 105HKD juste pour un thé soi-disant gratuit au début du repas, le serveur vous le dit à l'oral. Mais finalement il est taxé !! C'est une autre personne qui vous fait payer et vous montre la fameuse carte sur la taxe sur du thé ! Ils cachent le fameux papier plastifié d'avertissement sur la taxe de service et du thé, à 16$ par personnes ! Et tout autres sauces sont facturées !
